<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4374] Up default regions size from 256M to 1G</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4374</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4365&quot; title=&quot;Add a decent heuristic for region size&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4365&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4365&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; has some discussion of why we default for a table should tend to fewer bigger regions.  It doesn&apos;t look like this issue will be done for 0.92.  For 0.92, lets up default region size from 256M to 1G and talk up pre-split on table creation in manual.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12522805">HBASE-4374</key>
            <summary>Up default regions size from 256M to 1G</summary>
